deck: Daughter of the evil Rebborizan, wife of Gary Concord Sr., mother of Gary Concord Jr.
description:
The daughter of the evil dictator Rebborizan, who was overthrown by Gary Concord Sr., the first Ultra-Man. After her father's defeat, she and Concord fell in love and were married. Years later, shortly after the birth of their son, Rebborizan returned to seek revenge. The villain shot his "traitorous" daughter dead before Concord could stop him, but Concord immediately avenged her by strangling Rebborizan.

Years after her death, her son Gary Concord Jr. inherited his father's mantle as the second Ultra-Man.
name: Leandra

deck: 22nd-century dictator Rebborizan was overthrown by Gary Concord Sr., the first Ultra-Man.
description: A tyrannical dictator of the 22nd century, Rebborizan was overthrown by Gary Concord Sr., the first Ultra-Man. After the tyrant's defeat, Concord fell in love with Rebborizan's daughter Leandra and married her. Several years later, after the birth of the couple's son, Rebborizan returned for revenge. The villain shot his "traitorous" daughter dead before Concord could stop him, but Concord immediately avenged her by strangling Rebborizan.
name: Rebborizan

deck: New superpowered foe of the Flash
description:
Origin

Lummox is an average crook who has a super powered armored super suit, that gives him great strength and invulnerability.

Creation

Lummox was created by Brett Booth, Robert Venditti and Van Jensen. Lummox only appeared in one issue of The Flash, #41 - Yellow.

Major Story Arcs

The Flash: Zoom

For more information see: The Flash: Zoom

Lummox is attempting to rob a jewelry store in Central City when The Flash shows up. Lummox is able to get a lucky shot on The Flash, due to Professor Zoom distracting the hero. The Flash quickly regains the upper hand and is able to defeat Lummox by creating a vortex around him taking away his air.
name: Lummox

He immeadiately begun to menace the world. Kidnapped Eve (who he was fond of), and trampled on. Wrecking buildings, killing people just for the sake of being a giant. Wanted to rule the world.

Defeated the attacking Phantaliens, saving Earth.

Then he headed for Europe. But that wouldn`t be seen until his second appearance. Which wasn`t printed.

Unlike the cover of his first appearance shows, he had no armour. Didn`t need one.
